Kahoot! Quiz: Tasmanian Native Plant Propagation (Short Version)

Question Answer 1 Answer 2 Answer 3 Answer 4 Time Limit (sec) Correct Answer
Why use bottom heat for cuttings? Prevents fungus Speeds root growth Cools the leaves Sterilises media 20 Speeds root growth
Blackwood seeds need cold treatment. True False   20 False
Best pre-treatment for Banksia seed? Smoke water Hot water Cold Scarify 20 Smoke water
The '20% rule' limits what? Watering amount Fertiliser strength Collection from wild Shade cover 20 Collection from wild
Best method for tussock grass? Seed Division Cutting Grafting 20 Division
Myrtle Beech seeds can be stored for years. True False   20 False
First step for Botrytis mould? More mist Add fertiliser Remove sick cuttings Do nothing 20 Remove sick cuttings
IBA range for semi-hardwood cuttings? 500-1000 ppm 1000-2000 ppm 3000-4000 ppm 5000+ ppm 20 3000-4000 ppm
Sign of nitrogen deficiency? Purple leaves Yellow lower leaves Brown leaf tips Wilting 20 Yellow lower leaves
Best time to take cuttings? Midday Early morning Late afternoon Night 20 Early morning
Purpose of hardening off? Grow faster Prevent disease Adjust to outdoors Root deeper 20 Adjust to outdoors
Which seed must be sown fresh? Eucalyptus Acacia Banksia Nothofagus 20 Nothofagus
Best parent plant for cuttings? Old and flowering Young and healthy Recently watered Shaded 20 Young and healthy
Proteaceae need what type of mix? High nitrogen High phosphorus Low phosphorus Heavy clay 20 Low phosphorus
Purpose of misting cuttings? Feed them Cool leaves Wash pests Warm roots 20 Cool leaves
Permit needed for public land collection? Always Only for trees Only rare species Never 20 Always
How to stop Phytophthora spread? Water less Boot wash station More fertiliser Shade cloth 20 Boot wash station
Best container for eucalypts? Shallow tray Forestry tube Clay pot Seed flat 20 Forestry tube
Smoke water helps which group? Grasses Ferns Proteaceae Orchids 20 Proteaceae
What does IBA do? Kills fungus Feeds plant Stimulates roots Hardens off 20 Stimulates roots

