Perfect! I've transformed these written assessment questions into short, Kahoot-friendly quiz questions. They're now quick to read, test the same knowledge, but feel like a game rather than an exam.

---

Kahoot! Quiz: Tasmanian Native Plant Propagation (Assessment-Inspired)

Question Answer 1 Answer 2 Answer 3 Answer 4 Time Limit Correct Answer
Name one method of propagation. Fertilising Pruning Seed Watering 20 Seed
What is a parent plant? The oldest plant Plant you collect from Flowering plant Native plant 20 Plant you collect from
Best time to collect cuttings? Midday Late afternoon Early morning Night 20 Early morning
Why early morning collection? Plant is dry Plant is turgid Easier to see Cooler weather 20 Plant is turgid
How to store cuttings in field? In sun In water In plastic bag In dry box 20 In plastic bag
Softwood cuttings taken when? Winter Spring Autumn Year round 20 Spring
Hardwood cuttings taken when? Spring Summer Winter Autumn 20 Winter
Name one plant part for cuttings. Flower Fruit Stem Bark 20 Stem
Why use rooting hormone? Kills pests Hastens roots Feeds plant Prevents rot 20 Hastens roots
Name a container for cuttings. Garden bed Tube Bucket Wheelbarrow 20 Tube
Why bottom heat for cuttings? Cool roots Speed rooting Prevent disease Save energy 20 Speed rooting
Why mist cuttings? Keep tops cool Warm roots Feed them Wash them 20 Keep tops cool
What do seeds need to germinate? Fertiliser Moisture Pruning Shade 20 Moisture
Cold stratification uses what? Heat Cold and moist Smoke Scarification 20 Cold and moist
Name a scarification method. Boiling water Freezing Smoking Soaking 20 Boiling water
What seed needs boiling water? Eucalyptus Acacia Banksia Nothofagus 20 Acacia
How to sterilise tools? Water rinse Alcohol spray Soap wash Sun dry 20 Alcohol spray
Problem: seeds won't germinate? Too much light Wrong treatment Too much water Not enough air 20 Wrong treatment
Problem: cuttings wilt? Too much water Low humidity Too much light Cold roots 20 Low humidity
Do unrooted cuttings need fertiliser? Yes, daily Yes, weekly No Only liquid 20 No
When to fertilise seedlings? Before sowing After roots form Never Only in winter 20 After roots form
How to maintain secateurs? Keep wet Sharpen blades Store outside Never clean 20 Sharpen blades
Dispose diseased plants how? Compost Landfill Recycle Burn 20 Landfill
Name a nursery record. Weather forecast Propagation log Staff roster Budget plan 20 Propagation log
Daily greenhouse check? Staff attendance Temperature Plant prices Customer count 20 Temperature

